# Phase 3: Ongoing Mattermost Maintenance

> The server is live. Phase 3 keeps it that way.
>
> Phase 1 extracted Slack. Phase 2 imported it and cut over. Phase 3 is every
> subsequent week, month, quarter, and year of ongoing operation — OS patches,
> version bumps, backups you can actually restore from, drills, credential
> rotation, and a disaster-recovery playbook that produces an answer instead
> of a panic.

## Do This First

1. Open [START-HERE.md](references/START-HERE.md). It is the safe-next-action
   guide when you don't know which stage you need.
2. Copy `config.env.example` → `config.env`; fill in `MATTERMOST_URL`,
   `MATTERMOST_ADMIN_TOKEN`, `TARGET_HOST`, `POSTGRES_DSN`, `BACKUP_PATH`,
   `OFFSITE_REMOTE`, `SCRATCH_DB_URL`, `REBOOT_WINDOW_*`, `ROLLBACK_OWNER`.
3. Run `./scripts/doctor.sh`, then `./scripts/doctor.sh --require-remote`,
   then `./scripts/doctor.sh --require-mcp`. All three must report
   `Health score: N/N required passing (100%) — READY` before any stage runs.
4. Run `./maintain.sh health` to take a baseline. Archive the resulting
   `workdir-phase3/reports/latest-health.json`; it's the "before" for every
   change you'll make.
5. Schedule `./maintain.sh weekly-sweep` as a recurring agent run (see
   [WEEKLY-CADENCE.md](references/WEEKLY-CADENCE.md)).

## Batteries-Included Bootstrap

Phase 3 runs on the operator workstation (Mac / Windows / Linux) and talks to
the Mattermost host via SSH plus the admin HTTP API. Bring the workstation up
to spec:

```bash
./scripts/doctor.sh                       # baseline workstation checks
./scripts/bootstrap-tools.sh              # mmctl + rclone + psql + jq + at deps
./scripts/doctor.sh --require-remote      # probe SSH to TARGET_HOST
./scripts/install-mcp-servers.sh          # register Mattermost MCP for the agent
./scripts/doctor.sh --require-mcp         # confirm MCP registration
./scripts/smoke-test-phase3.sh            # dry-run every stage
```

- [TOOL-BOOTSTRAP.md](references/TOOL-BOOTSTRAP.md) — per-platform install matrix.
- [MATTERMOST-MCP-SETUP.md](references/MATTERMOST-MCP-SETUP.md) — drive the live
  Mattermost admin API from Claude Code / Codex without memorizing `mmctl` flags.
- Remote host-side changes are made exclusively through `./maintain.sh` stages;
  the bootstrap script only touches the workstation.

## Operator Library and Quote Bank

Full operator cards (HEALTH, UPDATE-OS, UPDATE-MM, BACKUP, DB-HEALTH, RESTORE,
REBOOT, ROTATE, INCIDENT, DR) with triggers, inputs, outputs, failure modes,
and copy-paste prompt modules live in
[OPERATOR-LIBRARY.md](references/OPERATOR-LIBRARY.md).

Load-bearing rules trace back to anchored citations in
[QUOTE-BANK.md](references/QUOTE-BANK.md) (Mattermost docs, PostgreSQL docs,
prior incident notes). If a quote's anchor disappears, the rule is retired;
agents treat the quote bank as authoritative over ad-hoc reasoning.

## Stop Immediately If

- `TARGET_HOST` is unreachable over SSH in `BatchMode=yes`
- `MATTERMOST_URL` returns non-200 on `/api/v4/system/ping` for more than 60 seconds
- `MATTERMOST_ADMIN_TOKEN` is invalid (403 on `/api/v4/users/me`)
- `BACKUP_PATH` is not writable on target
- `OFFSITE_REMOTE` is unreachable and the previous nightly backup failed to upload
- `SCRATCH_DB_URL` is unset when `restore-drill` was requested
- last `restore-drill` is older than 90 days **and** an `update-mattermost` was requested
- `ROLLBACK_OWNER` is unset when a destructive stage (`update-mattermost`,
  `disaster-recovery`) was requested

Any of the above blocks the stage with a fail-closed error; investigate before
re-running, do not force past.

## Canonical Default Path

```
1. Baseline health                 → ./maintain.sh health
2. Weekly sweep (automated)        → ./maintain.sh weekly-sweep
3. Monthly sweep (sweep + trend review)
4. Quarterly restore-drill         → ./maintain.sh restore-drill
5. Per-release Mattermost upgrade  → ./maintain.sh update-mattermost
6. Per-incident response           → prompts/incident-response.md
7. Annually: full DR rehearsal     → prompts/dr-drill.md
```

See [specs/OPERATING-MODEL.md](references/specs/OPERATING-MODEL.md) for how
the operator interacts with the agent across this cadence.

## Migration Threat Model (Ongoing Ops)

**Sensitive assets** in this phase:
- Mattermost admin PAT (full-admin API access)
- `POSTGRES_DSN` password (direct DB access)
- SSH private key for `TARGET_SSH_USER`
- `OFFSITE_REMOTE` credentials (rclone token/keys)
- Postmark / SMTP token (still valid post-cutover)
- Cloudflare API token (DNS + origin-cert rotation)
- `pg_dump` files on disk (full conversation history)
- `/opt/mattermost/data/` file attachments (if local-stored)

**Trust boundaries**: operator workstation, live Mattermost host, off-site backup
destination, Cloudflare edge, upstream Mattermost APT repo, scratch-DB host.

**Main failure classes** during ongoing ops:
- silent backup failure (backups running but corrupt or un-uploaded)
- version drift (skipped security releases accumulate)
- cert expiry (Cloudflare Origin CA has 15-year life; Let's Encrypt has 90-day)
- PAT / SSH credential staleness (no rotation cadence)
- reboot postponement (kernel patches without reboot → stale exploit surface)
- upgrade regression (missed pre-upgrade backup, no rollback path)
- restore-drill neglect (backups never actually verified)
- unnoticed host compromise (intrusion via unpatched service)

**Countermoves** enforced by this skill:
- Every stage writes an audit-trail JSON to `workdir-phase3/reports/`.
- `update-mattermost` refuses to run without a successful recent
  `restore-drill` and takes a pre-upgrade dump before changing anything.
- `doctor.sh --require-remote` refuses to run against a host whose SSH host
  key has changed without operator re-acknowledgement.
- `schedule-reboot` refuses to schedule outside the configured window.
- Credential rotation has its own `rotate-credentials` stage with a named
  approver from `ROLLBACK_OWNER`.

Full detail: [MIGRATION-THREAT-MODEL.md](references/MIGRATION-THREAT-MODEL.md)
and [SECURITY-HARDENING.md](references/SECURITY-HARDENING.md).

## Secret Handling

Secrets never go into git, never into `workdir-phase3/reports/` (the redactor
runs on every write), and never into agent chat history longer than necessary.

- Operator workstation keeps secrets in a password manager (1Password,
  Bitwarden, macOS Keychain).
- `config.env` stays local; the shipped `.gitignore` excludes it.
- Mattermost admin PAT rotates on a 90-day cadence via the `rotate-credentials`
  stage; old tokens are revoked in System Console.
- SSH keys rotate annually or on operator change; the `rotate-credentials`
  stage guides you through adding the new public key to `authorized_keys`
  before revoking the old one.
- Backup-destination keys (rclone / R2 / Storage Box) rotate annually.

Full detail: [playbooks/TOKEN-HANDLING.md](references/playbooks/TOKEN-HANDLING.md).

## Stage Map

| Stage | Purpose | Typical cadence | Idempotent? | Destructive? |
|-------|---------|-----------------|-------------|--------------|
| `health` | Live probe: HTTP, WS, SMTP, disk, PG, logs, services | weekly + on-demand | yes | no |
| `update-os` | `apt update` + security upgrades + `autoremove`; detects reboot-required | weekly (security) / monthly (all) | yes | no (until reboot) |
| `schedule-reboot` | Queue reboot in next off-hours window | after `update-os` flags reboot | idempotent if same window | yes (schedules a service restart) |
| `update-mattermost` | Pin target version; pre-dump + apt install + auto-rollback on failure | on release cadence | no (version change) | yes (service restart + schema migration) |
| `backup` | SSH-trigger pg_dump + rotate + off-site upload + hash verify | daily | yes | no |
| `db-health` | Postgres snapshot: sizing, connections, vacuum, locks, longest query | weekly | yes | no |
| `restore-drill` | Download latest backup, restore into scratch DB, verify row counts | quarterly | yes | yes (wipes SCRATCH_DB_URL) |
| `rotate-credentials` | Rotate PAT / SSH / off-site creds; operator-assisted | quarterly / annual | no | yes (revokes old creds) |
| `incident-response` | Manual playbook for user-reported problems | on alert | n/a (interactive) | varies |
| `disaster-recovery` | Rebuild on fresh host from off-site backup | annual drill / real DR | n/a (interactive) | yes (new host) |
| `weekly-sweep` | Combo: health → update-os → backup → db-health | weekly | yes | no (until reboot) |

## Canonical Pipeline (post-cutover flow)

```
                       ┌─────────────────┐
                       │  Phase 2 cutover │
                       │   (one-time)     │
                       └────────┬────────┘
                                │
                ┌───────────────┼───────────────┐
                │                               │
                ▼                               ▼
          [ first health ]              [ set up cron / cadence ]
                │                               │
                └──────────────┬────────────────┘
                               ▼
                  ┌─────────── weekly-sweep ──────────┐
                  │  health → update-os → backup →    │
                  │  db-health (+ schedule-reboot if  │
                  │  required)                        │
                  └───────────────┬───────────────────┘
                                  │
        ┌─────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────┐
        │                         │                         │
        ▼                         ▼                         ▼
  [ quarterly ]          [ per-release ]            [ unscheduled ]
  restore-drill          update-mattermost         incident-response
  rotate-creds           (with pre-dump +             (HEALTH red,
  (90-day PAT)            auto-rollback)               user reports,
                                                       disk full, etc.)
        │                         │                         │
        └─────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────┘
                                  ▼
                          [ annual DR drill ]
                          disaster-recovery
                          (full rebuild on
                          fresh host)
```

See [CROSS-PHASE-STATE-MACHINE.md](references/CROSS-PHASE-STATE-MACHINE.md)
for the full state diagram including incident-driven transitions.

## Script Contracts

| Script | Input | Output | Exit Behavior | Run When |
|--------|-------|--------|---------------|----------|
| `./maintain.sh <stage>` | `config.env` + stage name | `workdir-phase3/reports/<stage>-<ts>.json` + `latest-<stage>.json` symlink | fails on missing prerequisites or failed stage | any stage |
| `scripts/doctor.sh` | `config.env` | workstation health score | fails on missing required tools | before first run |
| `scripts/doctor.sh --require-remote` | + SSH access | + remote reachability | fails if SSH BatchMode fails | before any stage that touches target |
| `scripts/doctor.sh --require-mcp` | + MCP registration | + MCP connectivity | fails if MCP server can't be reached | before agent-driven operations |
| `scripts/bootstrap-tools.sh` | platform auto-detect | system deps installed | fails on unsupported platform | one-time workstation setup |
| `scripts/install-mcp-servers.sh` | Mattermost admin URL + PAT | MCP registered in Claude / Codex CLI + desktop | fails on missing CLI | one-time workstation setup |
| `scripts/smoke-test-phase3.sh` | `config.env` | dry-run report of all stages | non-zero on any stage dry-run failure | weekly sanity + after upgrades |
| `scripts/health-check.sh` | live target | `health-*.json` + markdown summary | non-zero on any red check | weekly |
| `scripts/os-update.sh` | live target | `os-update-*.json`, optional reboot flag | non-zero on apt error | monthly |
| `scripts/mattermost-upgrade.sh` | target, `MATTERMOST_TARGET_VERSION` | `mm-upgrade-*.json`, pre-upgrade dump | auto-rollback on failure | on release cadence |
| `scripts/db-backup.sh` | target, off-site creds | `backup-*.json`, SHA-256, rotation | non-zero on upload-verify fail | daily/weekly |
| `scripts/db-health.sh` | target | `db-health-*.json` + markdown | non-zero on red threshold | weekly |
| `scripts/restore-drill.sh` | off-site, `SCRATCH_DB_URL` | `restore-drill-*.json` | non-zero on row-count mismatch | quarterly |
| `scripts/schedule-reboot.sh` | target | `reboot-history.json` entry | non-zero if no off-hours window fits | after `update-os` flags reboot |
| `scripts/rotate-credentials.sh` | named creds scope | `rotate-credentials-*.json` + rotation audit | non-zero if rotation incomplete | quarterly/annual |
| `scripts/monitor-health.sh` | live target + duration | streaming JSONL of samples | never exits clean (Ctrl-C) | during an upgrade or incident |
| `scripts/verify-backup-integrity.py` | `OFFSITE_REMOTE` | per-backup SHA verification report | non-zero on any mismatch | quarterly or on suspicion |
| `scripts/compare-versions.py` | current + candidate | markdown diff of release notes | non-zero if no candidate available | before `update-mattermost` |
| `scripts/inspect-mattermost-log.py` | live log tail | structured error bucket report | n/a | during `health=red`, upgrades |
| `scripts/calls-plugin-health.sh` | Calls hostname + UDP port | Calls reachability JSON | non-zero on UDP probe fail | weekly (if Calls enabled) |
| `scripts/run-e2e-rehearsal.sh` | scratch host, latest backup | full rebuild dry-run report | non-zero on any phase fail | annually (DR drill) |

