## Done Means (per stage)

Phase 3 is a rolling "done." Each stage has its own pass criteria. Summary:

- `health` done when: overall ∈ {ok, yellow}, report written, any red escalated.
- `update-os` done when: `apt-get` returned 0, report written, reboot-required
  flag persisted if raised.
- `update-mattermost` done when: new version responds on `/api/v4/system/ping`,
  version matches target, pre-upgrade dump exists, health is ok.
- `backup` done when: dump written with matching SHA-256, uploaded off-site,
  remote SHA-256 verifies, rotation completed.
- `db-health` done when: all metrics within yellow threshold or flagged red
  with a note.
- `restore-drill` done when: pg_restore exits 0, row counts meet `RESTORE_MIN_*`
  thresholds, scratch DB was recreated cleanly.
- `rotate-credentials` done when: new creds work, old creds revoked, audit
  trail written.
- `disaster-recovery` done when: new host serves the same URL, backup restored,
  DNS swapped, post-mortem skeleton written.

Full matrix: [DONE-DEFINITION.md](references/DONE-DEFINITION.md).

## What This Skill Is Not

- **Not an observability platform.** If you need SLO dashboards, Prometheus
  scraping, or alerting on Mattermost metrics port 8067, use Grafana or
  Datadog; this skill runs point-in-time probes and does not replace
  continuous monitoring. See [OBSERVABILITY-LADDER.md](references/OBSERVABILITY-LADDER.md)
  for when to graduate.
- **Not an intrusion-detection system.** `fail2ban` and UFW are enabled by
  Phase 2's `provision` stage; this skill verifies they're still running but
  does not inspect logs for attacks.
- **Not a Mattermost feature configurator.** Use Mattermost's System Console
  for feature flags, plugins, user management. This skill only touches
  infrastructure.
- **Not a substitute for Mattermost Enterprise support.** For paid support and
  HA reference architectures, use Mattermost's commercial offering.

## Integration with Phases 1 and 2

This skill accepts the post-cutover state produced by Phase 2:

- `MATTERMOST_URL` + `MATTERMOST_ADMIN_TOKEN` — proven live at cutover.
- `TARGET_HOST` + `TARGET_SSH_USER=deploy` — non-root user created by Phase 2
  `provision`.
- `POSTGRES_DSN` — matches Phase 2's rendered config.
- `BACKUP_PATH=/var/backups/mattermost` — convention from Phase 2 `provision`.

If you are mid-migration and Phase 2 has not finished, this skill will refuse
to run. See [CROSS-PHASE-INTAKE-CONTRACT.md](references/CROSS-PHASE-INTAKE-CONTRACT.md).

