## Philosophy

1. **Boring is the goal.** The skill exists to make ongoing operations as
   uneventful as possible. Reports are short. Most weeks are green.
2. **Every artifact carries a hash.** Backups, dumps, uploads, configs. A
   hashless handoff is rejected.
3. **Fail closed on gates.** `update-mattermost` refuses without a verified
   restore-drill. `schedule-reboot` refuses outside the configured window.
   `rotate-credentials` refuses without ROLLBACK_OWNER.
4. **Idempotent or explicitly not.** Every stage declares whether re-running
   is safe. When it isn't, the operator library says so in big letters.
5. **Drills before disasters.** The quarterly restore-drill and annual DR
   drill are the difference between "backups exist" and "backups work."
6. **Automate reports, not decisions.** The agent runs the mechanics and
   writes the JSON; the human reads the one-paragraph summary and decides
   go / no-go / escalate.
